*We are looking for a facilitator to conduct workshops/sessions on Jetpack Compose during this timeline.*

ğŸ“Œ *What is Compose Camp?*
Compose Camp is a series of peer group learning sessions or hands-on workshops organised and facilitated by a GDSC campus for their Club members to gather knowledge around the basics of Kotlin, building UIs in Compose and more!


ğŸ“Œ *What we are looking for in a facilitator?*
    Preferably a student from the campus who has some familiarity with the basics of Android app Development using Kotlin.

    A student who has demonstrated leadership and presentation skills and is comfortable with public speaking.

    A student who can spend the next few weeks learning and facilitate app building sessions for your Club members using Compose. 

ğŸ“Œ *What will the facilitator get?*
    Content to help facilitate sessions on campus.

    An opportunity to lead Android training and facilitate app development in college.

    Participate in exclusive sessions planned by the GDSC team for Facilitators of the campaign.

ğŸ“Œ *What is Compose Camp?*

â›ºï¸ What is Compose Camp?

Compose Camp is a series of peer group learning sessions or hands-on workshops organized and facilitated by a GDSC campus for their Club members to gather knowledge around the basics of Kotlin, building UI's in Compose and more!

â›ºï¸ What to expect from the Compose Camp?

Android Studio Installation and Setup

Kotlin programming - language basics

How to build Android app UIs using Compose

Best practices of Modern Android Development

Choose open source repos with the label hacktoberfest

You need to submit a pull request to the repo.

An experience of how open source works. Contributions made will fetch you swags ğŸš€

22/12/2022, 10:14â€¯am - Wilfred Almeida(Gdsc): *Needlessly complicated process to get LoRs at TCET*

Choose faculty 
-> 
Take their permission
-> 
Print, sign and give the LoR consent form to Foram shah maam(HoC coordinator for COMP) 
->
Draft the LoRs 
-> 
Show the drafts to your chosen faulty members and make changes as requested 
-> 
Get the draft printed and signed by the faculty 
-> 
Take the draft to TnP cell and get their sign 
-> 
Take the draft to HoC cell and get their sign 
-> 
Take the drafts to Office no 1 and pay him money for LoR and get the receipt 
-> 
Take the drafts and receipts to HoC and get it printed on offical paper
 -> 
get the offical LoRs signed by faculty 
-> 
Get the official LoRs stamped by the office no1.
-> Congratulations you have your LoRs

ğŸ‘‰Cybersecurity is the process of protecting and recovering systems, networks, devices, and programs from the attacks. 
ğŸ‘‰In this session, we would be focusing on exploring the various components and fields involved in cybersecurity. 
ğŸ‘‰Also, we will be exploring the roadmap to get started with cybersecurity ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ’». 

ğŸ“Œ *Details* :
 *Date* :4th February 2023
 *Timing* : 4:00 - 6:00 pm
 *Speaker Name* : Arvind Jhawar 

 ğŸ“Œ *RSVP here to attend*  :
https://tinyurl.com/cybersecurity-gdsc

ğŸŸ¥ *Agenda for Session* :

1. Intro to cybersecurityğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ’»

2. Pre-requisite

16/05/2023, 6:31â€¯pm - +91 96532 96937: Dear GDSC TCET Team,

As I sit down to pen this message, a rush of memories from our journey together fills my heart. Over the course of our tenure, we've experienced a fascinating voyage of discovery, growth, and triumphs. From our first steps to our monumental achievements, each moment has been a testament to our spirit, dedication, and the power of teamwork. As we stand on the cusp of our final event together, it's hard not to feel a sense of nostalgia mingled with a bittersweet farewell.

Tomorrow, we come together one last time, not just as a team but as a family. A family that has seen the highs and lows, stuck together through thick and thin, laughed together, learned together, and most importantly, grew together. We've been through the gruelling late nights, the seemingly impossible deadlines, and the moments of doubt and challenge. But we stood tall, and we prevailed, because that's who we are.

I want to take a moment to express my gratitude to each one of you. You are the lifeblood of this team, and each of your contributions, big or small, has been instrumental in shaping our collective journey. I want to thank you for your resilience, your unwavering dedication, and your infectious enthusiasm that has kept us all going. It has been an honor to guide you, to learn from you, and to work alongside you.

As we approach our final event, let's remember what brought us together in the first place - our shared passion for technology, our commitment to learning, and our desire to make a difference. Let's make this event not just a culmination of our tenure, but a celebration of all that we have achieved together. Let's make it big, let's make it memorable, let's make it a testament to our journey.

This might be the end of our tenure, but it's not the end of our journey. The bonds we've forged, the lessons we've learned, and the memories we've created will always be a part of us. The friendships we've formed, the challenges we've overcome, the successes we've celebrated, they have all prepared us for the next stages of our lives.

As we part ways, remember this, GDSC TCET is not just about the events we've held or the projects we've completed. It's about the spirit of collaboration, the pursuit of knowledge, and the bonds of friendship. It's about the difference we've made and the lives we've touched.

Let's carry this spirit forward in our individual journeys. Let's continue to learn, grow, and strive for excellence. And no matter where we find ourselves in the future, let's always remember the time we spent together, the impact we made, and the family we formed.

Here's to one last hurrah, to a grand finale, to a beautiful ending of this chapter, and to the beginning of many more. Let's make tomorrow not just an event, but a beautiful memory that we will carry in our hearts forever.

With deepest affection and utmost gratitude,
Dhiraj Chauhan
Advisory, GDSC TCET
